# Website security assurance case for a public-facing web application.
# Demonstrates all LTAC element types and rendering options.

- Claim Security: The website is adequately secure against moderate threats
  - Context XScope: OWASP Top Ten threat model defines the threat scope (owasp-top10.pdf)
  - Strategy SArg: Security is argued by examining access control, data protection, and deployment
    - Claim ^Access
    - Claim ^Data
    - Claim Deployment: Deployment configuration follows security hardening guidelines
      - Evidence EvHarden: Server hardening checklist completed and signed off (hardening-checklist.pdf)
      - Context XProd: Production environment enforces HTTPS-only connections

- Claim Access: User access control prevents unauthorized actions
  - Assumption AAdmin: Site administrators follow the published access management policy
  - Strategy SAccess: Access control is argued by examining authentication and authorization
    - Claim AuthN: All users are authenticated before accessing protected resources
      - Evidence EvLogin: Login audit log shows no unauthorized access in last 90 days (audit.log)
      - Justification JMechanism: Password-plus-MFA provides industry-standard two-factor authentication
      - Context XLogPolicy: Log retention policy requires 90-day audit trail (log-policy.pdf)
    - Claim AuthZ: Users can only access resources appropriate to their role
      - Evidence EvRBAC: Role-based access control configuration review passed (rbac-review.pdf)
      - Claim AuthZAdmin: Administrative functions require elevated privilege {assumed}
    - Claim XSSFree: Cross-site scripting attacks are mitigated
      - Evidence EvCSP: Content Security Policy headers verified by automated scanner (csp-scan.pdf)
      - Relation R1: {counter}
        - Link EvPenTest
    - Claim SqlFree: SQL injection attacks are mitigated {defeated}
      - Evidence EvPenTest: Penetration test report identifies active vulnerabilities in multiple endpoints (pentest-2024.pdf)
      - Claim DBVuln: Active SQL injection vulnerability found in search endpoint {defeater}

- Claim Data: Sensitive user data is protected in transit and at rest
  - Context XRegulation: GDPR and applicable state privacy laws govern data handling (privacy-policy.pdf)
  - Claim AEncrypt: TLS 1.3 is correctly deployed on all public endpoints {axiomatic}
  - Strategy SData: Data protection is argued by examining encryption, minimization, and audit logging
    - Claim Encrypt: All sensitive data is encrypted in transit and at rest
      - Evidence EvTLS: TLS configuration scan achieves A+ rating (ssl-labs-report.pdf)
      - Evidence EvDB: Database-level encryption enabled and key management audited (db-audit.pdf)
    - Claim Minimise: Only necessary data is collected and retained per the privacy policy
      - Claim DataMap: The data flow diagram covers all personal data stores and flows {needssupport}
      - Justification JRetention: Data minimisation reduces breach impact and aids regulatory compliance
    - Claim AuditAccess: All sensitive data access events are logged and periodically reviewed {abstract}
  - Claim MetaClaim: This assurance case addresses all applicable data protection requirements {metaclaim}
